p: The data revealed that extracts 1Eâ€“6E displayed a statistically significant percentage of growth inhibition in a dose-dependent manner on all designated cell lines after 48 h and 72 h ( p < 0.05); however, that trend was not noticed after 24 h of treatment ( p > 0.05). Time-dependent growth inhibition was present only on the HeLa cell line with high statistical significance ( p < 0.0001), while a significant time-dependent effect was revealed only at the highest examined concentration on MRC-5 and MDA-MB 231 cells ( p < 0.05). On the other hand, the increase in growth inhibition of the SW480 cell line was independent of the exposure period.
